articleList.articleTitle: How to Hit a Triple Bodyweight Deadlift
articleList.articleDescription: Build Strength, Don't Test It One of the most common mistakes novice lifters make is testing their 1RM (one-rep max) and working at near-max percentages too often. Your tissues and nervous system can't constantly handle high intensities.
